Cap off the week with dinner and a show. 🌅🌊👇 

Grab your friends, family, or a date and head across the harbour for dinner at one of these local eateries:

@thecanteenns - A bright and cheery neighbourhood restaurant serving up approachable dishes influenced by classic French, Italian, and Nova Scotia cuisine,  packed with bold flavour, and sourced with seasonal local ingredients. (22 Portland St) 🦞🥂 

@sidehustlesnackbar - A modern, eclectic eatery offering a globally-inspired menu of casual-yet-refined bites and seasonal handcrafted cocktails. (21 Portland St) 🥟🍸 

@dearfriendbar - A cozy neighbourhood nook known for its inventive, playful cocktails, locally-sourced oysters, gourmet shareable plates, and late-night snacks. (67 Portland St) 🦪🍹

@newscotlandbrewing - A local taproom serving up an ever-changing menu of core and small-batch brews and mouthwatering comfort food. If you're a live music lover, put this spot at the top of your must-visit list. (16 Portland St) 🍻🎶 

@stone_pizza - An artisan pizza joint known for its extensive, crowd-pleasing menu that accommodates a variety of dietary needs including gluten-free, vegan, dairy-free, and keto-friendly options. (79 Alderney Dr) 🍕✨ 

@dorakudartmouth - A retro Japanese restaurant known for its incredible melt-in-your-mouth sushi and vibrant, fresh flavours. It's no question that this spot serves up some of the best Japanese cuisine in the Halifax region. (44 Ochterloney St) 🍣🍶 

@batteryparkbeer - A taproom and eatery featuring a rotating menu of local craft beer with a menu of farm-to-table fare, featuring gourmet burgers, sides, bar snacks and weekly chalkboard specials. (62 Ochterloney St) 🍔🍻 

Take your dessert to-go and make your way to Conrad's Beach at sunset. Get cozy on the beach with your treats and listen to the gentle lapping waves as the sun falls below the horizon for the dreamiest start to your weekend. 🌊🧁✨

📍 Conrad's Beach, Nova Scotia 
📷 @_giri_______

