Grab your pals, pack a blanket, and head out for the evening, Haligonian-style. 👇 

Make plans to spend the evening at the Halifax Common, a large urban park situated in the heart of Halifax. 🧺🌳✨

Before making your way over, grab an artisan sandwich or charcuterie box from @lukessmallgoods, or a fresh pizza from @lou.pecou to enjoy a picnic in the park. 🥪🍕☀️ 

Satisfy your sweet tooth with a cone of small-batch ice cream from @deedeesicecream. If sweet treats aren't your thing, this locally-loved eatery also serves up out-of-this-world burritos, perfect to pack for a picnic. 🍦🌯 

If you're in the mood to keep exploring after your picnic, make plans to visit the brand-new @goodrobot_commons this evening for their opening night. 🍻🤖 

Here are some other nearby spots to check out:
@ramblers.hfx - A cozy neighbourhood cafe & bar serving up craft beer, cider, and wine. Stop in for a drink and stay for the incredible live music. (5576 Cornwallis St) 🍎🎶 

@fieldguidehfx - Exceptional cocktails and decadent small plates served in an intimate atmosphere. (2076 Gottingen St) 🍹🦪 

@tusketfallsbrewing - A beer bar serving up decadent comfort food and craft brews sourced from their brewery in Tusket, Nova Scotia. (2220 Gottingen St) 🍔🍺 

@hopyardhalifax - A beer bar with a rotating menu of snacks, a large collection of vinyl to spin, board games, and more. (2103 Gottingen St) 🍻🎶

@thelocalhfx - A charming bar known for live music, pop-up kitchens, pool, and fantastic deals. (2037 Gottingen St) 🎱🍻 

What's your favourite Friday night destination? Tell us in the comments!

📍 Halifax Common
📷 @chouin23

