There's no better way to welcome the summer season than with a visit to your favourite patio. ☀️✨ 

We've rounded up 9 picture-perfect patios across the Halifax region to check out – grab your pals, soak up the sunshine, and celebrate the warm season at one of these local eateries.👇 

@barsabbia - Settle into a menu of tasty bar bites, wine, beer, and handcrafted cocktails, including an assorted spritz tower. (1475 Lower Water St) 🍊🥂 

@birchandanchor - Enjoy summery bites, beer, wine, and cocktails by the glass or pitcher oceanside. (367 Bedford Hwy)⁠ 🍤🍹

@lupin.dining - A gourmet farm-to-table experience in its truest essence with a  menu inspired by the seasonal flavours of Nova Scotia grown and harvested in their garden. (1196 West Petpeswick Rd)🍷🌿 

@gooddayns - Stop by for coffee, all-day breakfast, sandwiches, and pastries at this charming café. Looking for beer, wine, or cider? They've got you covered. (1480 Fall River Rd)⁠ 🧇☕️ 

@celtic.corner - Get cozy atop the stunning sunny rooftop patio overlooking the harbour. (69 Alderney Dr)⁠ 🌊☀️

@barkismet - A small family-owned restaurant and bar serving up fresh seafood, handmade pasta, inventive cocktails, and curated wines. (2733 Agricola St) 🐟🍝 

@boondocks.restaurant - Sit down to an extensive food and drink menu of crowd-pleasing favourites at this dreamy oceanfront patio. (6 Government Wharf Rd)⁠ 🌊🦞

@oxfordtaproom - Hidden among the trees, stop in for craft beer by @garrisonbrewing at this charming patio. (6418 Quinpool Rd)⁠ 🍻🌳

@tuna.blue - Enjoy a menu filled with fresh seafood dishes, pasta, steak, burgers, and more. (167 Shore Club Rd) 🌮🦀 ⁠

