Early risers are treated to a tranquil world in Halifax. 🌅🌊✨ 

Discover cozy cafés, vibrant street art, and the city’s captivating history, all bathed in the morning sun’s soft light. ☕🎨☀️ 

Here are just a few local cafés in Halifax’s downtown core to kickstart your morning.👇 

@birdsnesthalifax - A charming café serving breakfast, baked goods, soups, sandwiches, specialty coffees, and more. (1547 Barrington St) ☕🪺

@weirdharbour - A fun and cheery coffee shop offering an assortment of fresh baked goods, specialty coffees, and fast service. (1656 Barrington St) ☕⚓ 

@cabincoffeehfx - One of the oldest family-owned cafés in downtown Halifax, this rustic spot serves up a variety of decadent treats, soups, sandwiches, and coffees. (1554 Hollis St) ☕🍁 

@lefrenchfix - A cozy little French café offering delicate pastries and specialty coffees. (5233 Prince St) ☕🥐 

What’s your favourite local Halifax café? Tell us in the comments!👇 

📍 Downtown Halifax, Nova Scotia
📷 @riazoozeer

